---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service - Drizby" description="Terms of Service for Drizby. Read the terms and conditions governing your use of the Drizby platform and Drizby Cloud." canonicalPath="/terms">
  <main class="legal-page">
    <div class="legal-container">
      <header class="legal-header">
        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: March 2026</p>
      </header>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of the Drizby websites, products, and services (collectively, the "Service"). Drizby is an open-source business intelligence platform with a managed cloud offering ("Drizby Cloud"). By accessing or using the Service, you agree to be bound by these Terms.</p>
        <p>You must be at least 13 years of age to use the Service. By using the Service, you represent and warrant that you meet this age requirement.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>2. Definitions</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>"Terms"</strong> refers to these Terms of Service.</li>
          <li><strong>"Drizby"</strong> refers to the open-source BI platform, including the self-hosted software and Drizby Cloud.</li>
          <li><strong>"User"</strong> refers to any individual who accesses or uses the Service.</li>
          <li><strong>"Customer"</strong> refers to any individual or entity that subscribes to a paid Service level.</li>
          <li><strong>"Agreement" or "Contract"</strong> refers to these Terms together with any applicable order form or subscription agreement.</li>
          <li><strong>"Service"</strong> refers to all Drizby products, software, websites, and related services.</li>
          <li><strong>"Service Level"</strong> refers to the tier of service (Free or Paid) selected by the User or Customer.</li>
          <li><strong>"Website"</strong> refers to <a href="https://www.drizby.com">www.drizby.com</a> and all associated subdomains.</li>
          <li><strong>"You" / "Your"</strong> refers to the User or Customer accessing the Service.</li>
          <li><strong>"Customer Content"</strong> refers to all data, information, and materials uploaded, submitted, or transmitted by You through the Service.</li>
          <li><strong>"We" / "Our"</strong> refers to Drizby and its operator, Clifton Cunningham.</li>
          <li><strong>"Company"</strong> refers to Clifton Cunningham, contactable at <a href="mailto:legal@drizby.com">legal@drizby.com</a>.</li>
          <li><strong>"Use" / "Using" / "Usage"</strong> refers to any access to, interaction with, or utilisation of the Service.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>3. Usage Rules</h2>
        <p>By using the Service, you agree to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Use the Service only for lawful purposes and in compliance with all applicable laws and regulations.</li>
          <li>Maintain the security of your account credentials and promptly notify us of any unauthorised access.</li>
          <li>Not use the Service in any way that could damage, disable, or impair the Service or interfere with other users.</li>
          <li>Not attempt to gain unauthorised access to any part of the Service, other accounts, or systems.</li>
          <li>Comply with any additional guidelines or policies we publish regarding specific features.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>4. Service Levels</h2>
        <div class="legal-card">
          <h3>Free - Self-Hosted Open Source</h3>
          <p>Drizby is available as open-source software under the MIT License. You may download, install, modify, and run Drizby on your own infrastructure at no cost. The self-hosted version is provided "as-is" without any service level guarantees.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="legal-card">
          <h3>Paid - Drizby Cloud</h3>
          <p>Drizby Cloud is a managed hosting service that provides a fully maintained Drizby instance. Paid plans include hosting, maintenance, backups, and support as described on the pricing page. Specific service level agreements may apply as detailed in your subscription agreement.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>5. Agreement Terms</h2>
        <p><strong>Free tier:</strong> These Terms apply for as long as you use the self-hosted open-source version of Drizby. You may cease using the software at any time.</p>
        <p><strong>Paid tier:</strong> Your paid subscription begins on the date of purchase and continues for the subscription period selected. Subscriptions automatically renew unless cancelled before the end of the current billing period.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>6. Cancellation and Refund Policy</h2>
        <div class="legal-card">
          <h3>30-Day Money-Back Guarantee</h3>
          <p>All new Drizby Cloud subscriptions include a 30-day money-back guarantee. If you are not satisfied with the Service within the first 30 days of your initial subscription, you may request a full refund.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="legal-card">
          <h3>Subscription Cancellation</h3>
          <p>You may cancel your subscription at any time through your account settings or by contacting <a href="mailto:legal@drizby.com">legal@drizby.com</a>. Upon cancellation, your subscription will remain active until the end of the current billing period, after which it will not renew.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="legal-card">
          <h3>Refund Process</h3>
          <p>Refund requests should be sent to <a href="mailto:legal@drizby.com">legal@drizby.com</a>. Approved refunds will be processed within 10 business days to the original payment method.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="legal-card">
          <h3>Exceptions</h3>
          <p>Refunds may not be available in cases of Terms of Service violations, abuse of the refund policy, or where the Service has been substantially consumed during the refund period.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>7. Privacy</h2>
        <p>Your privacy is important to us. Our collection and use of personal data is governed by our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>, which is incorporated into these Terms by reference. By using the Service, you consent to the practices described in the Privacy Policy.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>8. Customer Content and Content Ownership</h2>
        <p>You retain all rights, title, and interest in your Customer Content. By using the Service, you grant us a limited, non-exclusive licence to process, store, and display your Customer Content solely as necessary to provide the Service.</p>
        <p>We do not claim ownership of your Customer Content. We will not access, use, or share your Customer Content except as required to operate and improve the Service, or as required by law.</p>
        <p>You are solely responsible for the legality, reliability, and appropriateness of your Customer Content. You represent and warrant that you have all necessary rights to upload and use your Customer Content with the Service.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>9. Identity</h2>
        <p>You agree to provide accurate, current, and complete information during registration and to keep your account information updated. You are responsible for all activity that occurs under your account. You must not impersonate any person or entity, or misrepresent your affiliation with any person or entity.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>10. Reverse Engineering</h2>
        <p>While Drizby's core software is open source, you shall not reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble any proprietary components of the Drizby Cloud service, including but not limited to infrastructure configurations, proprietary extensions, and deployment tooling, except to the extent expressly permitted by applicable law.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>11. Restrictions</h2>
        <p>You agree not to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Allow use by anyone under the age of 13.</li>
          <li>Upload, store, or process data that you do not have authorisation to use.</li>
          <li>Use automated tools to scrape, crawl, or extract data from the Service without prior written consent.</li>
          <li>Use the Service to transmit malware, spam, or any harmful content.</li>
          <li>Resell, redistribute, or sublicence the Drizby Cloud service without authorisation.</li>
          <li>Circumvent, disable, or interfere with security features of the Service.</li>
          <li>Use the Service to compete directly with Drizby without disclosure.</li>
          <li>Engage in any activity that disrupts or places an unreasonable burden on the Service infrastructure.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>12. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>The Drizby open-source software is released under the MIT License. All rights not expressly granted under the MIT License are reserved.</p>
        <p>The Drizby name, logo, and branding are trademarks of Clifton Cunningham. You may not use these marks without prior written permission, except as necessary to refer to the Drizby project in a descriptive capacity.</p>
        <p>Proprietary components of Drizby Cloud, including but not limited to cloud infrastructure, deployment systems, and managed service tooling, are the intellectual property of Clifton Cunningham and are not covered by the MIT License.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>13. No Warranties</h2>
        <p>THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, WHETHER EXPRESS, IMPLIED, OR STATUTORY. WE DISCLAIM ALL WARRANTIES, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT.</p>
        <p>We do not warrant that the Service will be uninterrupted, error-free, secure, or free of viruses or other harmful components. Your use of the Service is at your sole risk.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>14. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, IN NO EVENT SHALL CLIFTON CUNNINGHAM BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR ANY LOSS OF PROFITS, REVENUE, DATA, OR BUSINESS OPPORTUNITIES ARISING FROM YOUR USE OF THE SERVICE.</p>
        <p>Our total aggregate liability for all claims arising from or related to these Terms or the Service shall not exceed the total amount paid by you to us in the twelve (12) months preceding the event giving rise to the claim.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>15. Indemnification</h2>
        <p>You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless Clifton Cunningham from and against any claims, liabilities, damages, losses, costs, or expenses (including reasonable legal fees) arising from or related to: (a) your use of the Service; (b) your Customer Content; (c) your violation of these Terms; or (d) your violation of any rights of a third party.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>16. Non-Disclosure</h2>
        <p>Each party agrees that any confidential or proprietary information disclosed by one party to the other in connection with the Service shall be kept confidential and shall not be disclosed to any third party without prior written consent. This obligation of confidentiality shall survive termination of these Terms for a period of three (3) years.</p>
        <p>Confidential information does not include information that: (a) is or becomes publicly available through no fault of the receiving party; (b) was known to the receiving party prior to disclosure; (c) is independently developed without use of confidential information; or (d) is required to be disclosed by law.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>17. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the United Kingdom, without regard to conflict of law principles. Any disputes arising from these Terms shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>18. Contact</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions about these Terms of Service, please contact us:</p>
        <div class="legal-card">
          <p>Email: <a href="mailto:legal@drizby.com">legal@drizby.com</a></p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .legal-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .legal-header h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--text) 0%, var(--accent-hover) 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .legal-updated {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .legal-section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .legal-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .legal-section h3 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--accent-hover);
  }

  .legal-section p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-section ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-section ul li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-section ul li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.65em;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent);
  }

  .legal-section strong {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .legal-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-card p {
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .legal-card p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .legal-header h1 {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }
  }
</style>
